reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great customer service
reviews.reviewText: I have used the camera for almost 2 years and it provided me video avidence to fight with a police man in Philadelphia traffic court and I won, so I got back over $150. I am impressed by the customer support that I got from the seller. I want to say it's the best one. Camera is also super stable. It will be even better if it has a touch screen. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Does not always record
reviews.reviewText: We have had 2 of these cameras now for several months and we have never had a reason to pull the card and see what the camera is actually recording, until today. There are several months worth of random getting in and out of the vehicle but there are very little recordings of us driving. So basically when you hear the camera start up it records for a short time then seems to shut off until you stop the vehicle and then it begins recording you getting out of the vehicle. Not happy. Not impressed. Would not recommend!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: We bought two. Both of them have power problems. They will randomly turn off, and if you’re not watching, you will go unprotected.One of them has now completely failed after 9 months. Won’t stay on, says insert SD card.We did get one good use- showed another driver cutting me off before a crash. Saved me a ticket and insurance claim. Caveat Emptor

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars The internal battery does not last.
reviews.reviewText: Seems like a good camera, but the internal battery does not last - after some time cannot disconnect it from the car's power supply to show the video to an officer if necessary, since the camera would turn off right away due to low charge. In case of an accident, this prevents you from setting the story straight with a police officer right at the sight of the accident.
Price was good and product works when I need it. Took a few seconds to adjust the settings to fit how I want it to run

Bildqualität völlig ausreichend, auch bei Nacht noch gute Ausleuchtung. Gegenlicht kann die Kamera nicht gut ausgleichen, da ist dann nicht viel zu erkennen, aber bei einem Preis von 36,- € kann man nicht meckern. Verwendung von Speicherkarten bis max. 64 GB ist völlig ausreichend. Größere Speicherkarten werden nicht erkannt, habe es mit einer 200 GB Speicherkarten probiert, wurde nicht erkannt. Bei einer Auflösung von 1920 x 1280 sind die einminütigen Clips 250 MB groß und liefern eine gute Qualität. Bei einer Auflösung von 1440 x 1080 (220 MB) ist die Qualität immer noch ausreichend gut, so daß Kennzeichen aus nächster Nähe erkannt werden. Die nächst kleinere Auflösung habe ich nicht ausprobiert.
